This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of universal dependencies, which is a common tool in computational linguistics. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper discusses unsupervised algorithms and their advantages over supervised models. 

Furthermore, the paper mentions the use of compositional operations, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, these two sub-categories are also likely candidates.
